t kinds of content by blocking or throttling connection speeds or offering paid prioritization for different internet traffic. The FCC has sought to accomplish this by reclassifying ISPs as common carriers under Title II of the Communications Act, giving the agency more regulatory authority over them.</p></div><span class="mb-8 font-polysans text-15 font-medium leading-150 tracking-1 text-gray-13 "><a class="inline-block shadow-underline-black hover:shadow-highlight-franklin" href="/2024/4/25/24140157/fcc-vote-restore-net-neutrality-rosenworcel-biden">Read Article &gt;</a></span></div></div></div></li><li role="article" class="mx-[-16px] mb-40 mt-[-40px] px-16 last:mb-0 md:mx-0 md:px-0" id="stream-entry-a493b5c7-a885-47cb-99c5-e81338269b94"><div class="border-solid border-blurple-df pt-40 sm:border-b-0 border-b"><div class="mb-40"><div><div class="mb-10 flex items-center"><div class="absolute left-[-2px] hidden h-6 w-12 border-y-2 border-white bg-[#DFCFFF] md:block"></div><div class="relative mr-8 block h-[36px] w-[36px] flex-none overflow-hidden rounded-full border border-solid border-gray-ef bg-[#DFCFFF]"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0"><img alt="Lauren Feiner" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" class="rounded-full" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover"/><noscript><img alt="Lauren Feiner" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;ob