mbor/0x0:2040x1360/2400x1600/filters:focal(1020x680:1021x681):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/11515083/acastro_180608_1777_net_neutrality_0002.jpg 2400w" src="https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/2400x1600/filters:focal(1020x680:1021x681):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/11515083/acastro_180608_1777_net_neutrality_0002.jpg"/></noscript></span><div class="duet--media--caption pt-6 font-polysans-mono text-12 font-light leading-130 tracking-1"> <cite class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup inline not-italic text-gray-63 dark:text-gray-bd [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-gray-63 [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-gray-bd dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-gray [&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray-63 dark:[&amp;&gt;a]:text-gray-bd dark:[&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray">Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</cite></div></figure></div></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph my-12 font-fkroman text-17 leading-150 text-gray-13 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">After five years in a shallow grave, the FCC has revived the rules meant to force internet service providers (ISPs) like Comcast and Verizon to treat all traffic equally. The agency voted in favor of a notice of proposed rulemaking Thursday, taking its first step toward reinstating net neutrality. </p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph my-12 font-fkroman text-17 leading-150 text-gray-13 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">“Today, there is no expert agency ensuring that the internet is fast, open, and fair. And for everyone, everywhere to enjoy the full benefits of the internet age, internet access needs to be more than just accessible and affordable,” Chairwoman Jessica Rosenworcel said ahead of Thursday’s vote. “The internet needs to be open.” The notice was supported by Rosenworcel and Democratic commissioners Anna Gomez and Geoffrey Starks; it was opposed by Republican commissioners Brendan Carr and Nathan Simington.</p></div><span class="mb-8 font-polysans text-15 font-medium leading-150 tracking-1 text-gray-13 "><a class="inline-block shadow-underline-black hover:shadow-highlight-franklin" href="/2023/10/19/23922810/fcc-net-neutrality-proposed-rulemaking-vote">Read Article &gt;</a></span></div></div></div></li><li role="article" class="mx-[-16px] mb-40 mt-[-40px] px-16 last:mb-0 md:mx-0 md:px-0" id="stream-entry-3ed79b9c-c33e-42ae-afc9-eb323e23ce81"><div class="border-solid border-blurple-df pt-40 sm:border-b-0 border-b"><div class="mb-40"><div><div class="mb-10 flex items-center"><div class="absolute left-[-2px] hidden h-6 w-12 border-y-2 border-white bg-[#DFCFFF] md:block"></div><div class="relative mr-8 block h-[36px] w-[36px] flex-none overflow-hidden rounded-full border border-solid border-gray-ef bg-[#DFCFFF]"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0"><img alt="" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" class="rounded-full" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover"/><noscript><img alt="" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover" class="rounded-full" sizes="36px" srcSet="/icons/default_headshot.png 16w, /icons/default_headshot.png 32w, /icons/default_headshot.png 48w, /icons/default_headshot.png 64w, /icons/default_headshot.png 96w, /icons/default_headshot.png 128w, /icons/default_headshot.png 256w, /icons/default_headshot.png 376w, /icons/default_headshot.png 384w, /icons/default_headshot.png 415w, /icons/default_headshot.png 480w, /icons/default_headshot.png 540w, /icons/default_headshot.png 640w, /icons/default_headshot.png 750w, /icons/default_headshot.png 828w, /icons/default_headshot.png 1080w, /icons/default_headshot.png 1200w, /icons/default_headshot.png 1440w, /icons/default_headshot.png 1920w, /icons/default_headshot.png 2048w, /icons/default_headshot.png 2400w" src="/icons/default_headshot.png"/></noscript></span></div><div class="font-polysans text-11 uppercase leading-130 tracking-12 text-blurple"><p class="mb-2 font-bold">Sep 26, 2023</p><p><span><a class="hover:shadow-underline-blurple" href="/authors/jess-weatherbed">Jess Weatherbed</a></span><span><span> and </span><a class="hover:shadow-underline-blurple" href="/authors/adi-robertson">Adi Robertson</a></span></p></div></div><h2 class="mb-16 mt-12 font-polysans text-22 font-bold leading-100 tracking-1 text-gray-13 md:mb-14 md:text-24"><a class="hover:shadow-underline-black" href="/2023/9/26/23890527/fcc-net-neutrality-rules-law-usa-internet-access">FCC announces plans to resurrect net neutrality rules</a></h2><div class="w-full shrink-0 lg:basis-[600px]"><div class="md:pl-0"><figure class="duet--article--lede-image w-full"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:relative"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;padding-top:66.63636363636364%"></span><img alt="28th Annual Paley International Council Summit" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding="async" data-nimg="responsive" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover"/><noscript><img alt="28th Annual Paley International Council Summit" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-nimg="responsive" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover" sizes="(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 100px), (max-width: 1180px) 700px, 600px" srcSet="https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/16x11/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 16w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/32x21/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 32w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/48x32/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 48w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/64x43/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 64w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/96x64/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 96w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/128x85/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 128w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/256x171/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 256w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/376x251/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 376w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/384x256/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 384w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/415x277/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 415w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/480x320/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 480w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/540x360/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 540w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/640x427/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 640w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/750x500/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 750w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/828x552/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 828w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/1080x720/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 1080w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/1200x800/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 1200w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/1440x960/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 1440w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/1920x1280/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 1920w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/2048x1365/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 2048w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/2400x1600/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg 2400w" src="https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:3030x2020/2400x1600/filters:focal(1515x1010:1516x1011):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24953538/1440125578.jpg"/></noscript></span><div class="duet--media--caption pt-6 font-polysans-mono text-12 font-light leading-130 tracking-1"> <cite class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup inline not-italic text-gray-63 dark:text-gray-bd [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-gray-63 [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-gray-bd dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-gray [&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray-63 dark:[&amp;&gt;a]:text-gray-bd dark:[&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray">Photo by Steven Ferdman / Getty Images</cite></div></figure></div></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph my-12 font-fkroman text-17 leading-150 text-gray-13 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">The US Federal Communications Commission (FCC) has <a href="https://docs.fcc.gov/public/attachments/DOC-397235A1.pdf">announced plans to reinstate</a> landmark net neutrality rules meant to guarantee fair access to the internet and its information, five years after they were <a href="/2019/7/9/20687903/net-neutrality-was-repealed-a-year-ago-whats-happened-since">repealed by then-president Donald Trump</a> in 2018.</p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph my-12 font-fkroman text-17 leading-150 text-gray-13 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">Previous <a href="/2015/2/26/8114265/fcc-ruling-net-neutrality-victory-internet-title-ii">net neutrality rules adopted in 2015</a> classified broadband service under public utility rules and prevented internet service providers from blocking websites, throttling traffic, or charging more for faster access to certain services. According to FCC Chair Jessica Rosenworcel, the commission is expected to conduct an initial vote on reinstating these rules next month during an October 19th meeting.</p></div><span class="mb-8 font-polysans text-15 font-medium leading-150 tracking-1 text-gray-13 "><a class="inline-block shadow-underline-black hover:shadow-highlight-franklin" href="/2023/9/26/23890527/fcc-net-neutrality-rules-law-usa-internet-access">Read Article &gt;</a></span></div></div></div></li><li role="article" class="mx-[-16px] mb-40 mt-[-40px] px-16 last:mb-0 md:mx-0 md:px-0" id="stream-entry-0c1ebda0-cbb3-4be9-b1a9-e554edb1aa0e"><div class="border-solid border-blurple-df pt-40 sm:border-b-0 border-b"><div class="mb-40"><div><div class="mb-10 flex items-center"><div class="absolute left-[-2px] hidden h-6 w-12 border-y-2 border-white bg-[#DFCFFF] md:block"></div><div class=