duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/540x360/filters:focal(1020x680:1021x681):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/11516257/acastro_180608_1777_net_neutrality_0003.jpg 540w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/640x427/filters:focal(1020x680:1021x681):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/11516257/acastro_180608_1777_net_neutrality_0003.jpg 640w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/750x500/filters:focal(1020x680:1021x681):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/11516257/acastro_180608_1777_net_neutrality_0003.jpg 750w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/828x552/filters:focal(1020x680:1021x681):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/11516257/acastro_180608_1777_net_neutrality_0003.jpg 828w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/1080x720/filters:focal(1020x680:1021x681):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/11516257/acastro_180608_1777_net_neutrality_0003.jpg 1080w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/1200x800/filters:focal(1020x680:1021x681):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/11516257/acastro_180608_1777_net_neutrality_0003.jpg 1200w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/1440x960/filters:focal(1020x680:1021x681):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/11516257/acastro_180608_1777_net_neutrality_0003.jpg 1440w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/1920x1280/filters:focal(1020x680:1021x681):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/11516257/acastro_180608_1777_net_neutrality_0003.jpg 1920w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/2048x1365/filters:focal(1020x680:1021x681):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/11516257/acastro_180608_1777_net_neutrality_0003.jpg 2048w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/2400x1600/filters:focal(1020x680:1021x681):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/11516257/acastro_180608_1777_net_neutrality_0003.jpg 2400w" src="https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/2400x1600/filters:focal(1020x680:1021x681):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/11516257/acastro_180608_1777_net_neutrality_0003.jpg"/></noscript></span><div class="duet--media--caption pt-6 font-polysans-mono text-12 font-light leading-130 tracking-1"> <cite class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup inline not-italic text-gray-63 dark:text-gray-bd [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-gray-63 [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-gray-bd dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-gray [&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray-63 dark:[&amp;&gt;a]:text-gray-bd dark:[&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray">Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</cite></div></figure></div></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph my-12 font-fkroman text-17 leading-150 text-gray-13 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">Today, the FCC’s Restoring Internet Freedom Order takes effect, effectively repealing net neutrality protections in the US. The effects probably won’t be sudden; <a href="/2018/6/11/17439456/net-neutrality-dead-ajit-pai-fcc-internet">we’ve explained what might happen</a> without the rules and what’s already happened since the vote last year. But no matter what happens this week, repeal opens the door to some real abuses of internet service providers’ power — not hypothetical scenarios, but real predatory practices we’ve already seen in the past.</p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph my-12 font-fkroman text-17 leading-150 text-gray-13 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">These incidents show how complicated the issue of net neutrality is: all of these transgressions happened after the 2005 Internet Policy Statement, which laid out four “open internet” principles that would guide the agency’s decisions. Some happened during periods where firm rules were standing, others during periods when they’d been struck down. Companies reconsidered their choices because of public outcry, official investigations, and practical changes in technology. So while today is a disappointing day for net neutrality, keeping internet companies in check isn’t just about having the right rules in place. It’s about having regulators and an American public that will make trouble for anybody breaking them.</p></div><span class="mb-8 font-polysans text-15 font-medium leading-150 tracking-1 text-gray-13 "><a class="inline-block shadow-underline-black hover:shadow-highlight-franklin" href="/2018/6/11/17438638/net-neutrality-violation-history-restoring-internet-freedom-order">Read Article &gt;</a></span></div></div></div></li><li role="article" class="mx-[-16px] mb-40 mt-[-40px] px-16 last:mb-0 md:mx-0 md:px-0" id="stream-entry-cd84b292-039e-4560-a0f6-9caaaf5929cd"><div class="border-solid border-blurple-df pt-40 sm:border-b-0 border-b"><div class="mb-40"><div><div class="mb-10 flex items-center"><div class="absolute left-[-2px] hidden h-6 w-12 border-y-2 border-white bg-[#DFCFFF] md:block"></div><div class="relative mr-8 block h-[36px] w-[36px] flex-none overflow-hidden rounded-full border border-solid border-gray-ef bg-[#DFCFFF]"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0"><img alt="Makena Kelly" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" class="rounded-full" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover"/><noscript><img alt="Makena Kelly" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover" class="rounded-full" sizes="36px" srcSet="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 16w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 32w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 48w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 64w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 96w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 128w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 256w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 376w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 384w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 415w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 480w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 540w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 640w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 750w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 828w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 1080w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 1200w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 1440w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 1920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 2048w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg 2400w" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6rbtH96lmugb5WVaVjr1zetIzG4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195831/MAKENA_KELLY.0.jpg"/></noscript></span></div><div class="font-polysans text-11 uppercase leading-130 tracking-12 text-blurple"><p class="mb-2 font-bold">Jun 11, 2018</p><p><span><a class="hover:shadow-underline-blurple" href="/authors/makena-kelly">Makena Kelly</a></span></p></div></div><h2 class="mb-16 mt-12 font-polysans text-22 font-bold leading-100 tracking-1 text-gray-13 md:mb-14 md:text-24"><a class="hover:shadow-underline-black" href="/2018/6/11/17439456/net-neutrality-dead-ajit-pai-fcc-internet">Net neutrality is dead — what now?</a></h2><div class="w-full shrink-0 lg:basis-[600px]"><div class="relative w-full bg-black" style="padding-bottom:56.25%"></div></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph my-12 font-fkroman text-17 leading-150 text-gray-13 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">As of June 11th, the legal protections against content discrimination on the internet are gone. As far as the FCC is concerned, net neutrality is dead. </p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph my-12 font-fkroman text-17 leading-150 text-gray-13 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">The policy’s fate was sealed back in December 2017, when FCC chairman Ajit Pai’s Restoring Internet Freedom Order was approved in a 3-2 vote along party lines. Pai’s order, which goes into effect today, rolls back the net neutrality protections that were put in place by former chairman Tom Wheeler. They promise — in name, at least — unrestricted access to online content minus the burden of regulation. But in fact, the new ruling clears the way for massive internet service providers to do practically whatever they like — including paid prioritization, throttling, and otherwise messing with traffic as it moves across the internet. It will take a long time to see the practical effects of the new rules, but make no mistake: this is a big deal, and it’s the first step in a long, slow process that will reshape the internet in very ugly ways.</p></div><span class="mb-8 font-polysans text-15 font-medium leading-150 tracking-1 text-gray-13 "><a class="inline-block shadow-underline-black hover:shadow-highlight-franklin" href="/2018/6/11/17439456/net-neutrality-dead-ajit-pai-fcc-internet">Read Article &gt;</a></span></div></div></div></li><li role="article" class="mx-[-16px] mb-40 mt-[-40px] px-16 last:mb-0 md:mx-0 md:px-0" id="stream-entry-4e3cb885-85d9-484f-9f8e-eb5055083eb4"><div class="border-solid border-blurple-df pt-40 sm:border-b-0 border-b"><div class="mb-40"><div><div class="mb-10 flex items-center"><div class="absolute left-[-2px] hidden h-6 w-12 border-y-2 border-white bg-[#DFCFFF] md:block"></div><div class="relative mr-8 block h-[36px] w-[36px] flex-none overflow-hidden rounded-full border border-solid border-gray-ef bg-[#DFCFFF]"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0"><img alt="" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" class="rounded-full" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover"/><noscript><img alt="" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover" class="rounded-full" sizes="36px" srcSet="/icons/default_headshot.png 16w, /icons/default_headshot.png 32w, /icons/default_headshot.png 48w, /icons/default_headshot.png 64w, /icons/default_headshot.png 96w, /icons/default_headshot.png 128w, /icons/default_headshot.png 256w, /icons/default_headshot.png 376w, /icons/default_headshot.png 384w, /icons/default_headshot.png 415w, /icons/default_headshot.png 480w, /icons/default_headshot.png 540w, /icons/default_headshot.png 640w, /icons/default_headshot.png 750w, /icons/default_headshot.png 828w, /icons/default_headshot.png 1080w, /icons/default_headshot.png 1200w, /icons/default_headshot.png 1440w, /icons/default_headshot.png 1920w, /icons/default_headshot.png 2048w, /icons/default_headshot.png 2400w" src="/icons/default_headshot.png"/></noscript></span></div><div class="font-polysans text-11 uppercase leading-130 tracking-12 text-blurple"><p class="mb-2 font-bold">Dec 15, 2017</p><p><span><a class="hover:shadow-underline-blurple" href="/authors/russell-brandom">Russell Brandom</a></span><span><span> and </span><a class="hover:shadow-underline-blurple" href="/authors/adi-robertson">Adi Robertson</a></span></p></div></div><h2 class="mb-16 mt-12 font-polysans text-22 font-bold leading-100 tracking-1 text-gray-13 md:mb-14 md:text-24"><a class="hover:shadow-underline-black" href="/2017/12/15/16780564/net-neutrality-is-dead-what-happens-next">Net neutrality is dead — what happens next?</a></h2><div class="w-full shrink-0 lg:basis-[600px]"><div class="md:pl-0"><figure class="duet--article--lede-image w-full"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:relative"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;padding-top:66.63636363636364%"></span><img alt="" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding="async" data-nimg="responsive" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover"/><noscript><img alt="" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-nimg="responsive" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover" sizes="(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 100px), (max-width: 1180px) 700px, 600px" srcSet="https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/16x11/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 16w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/32x21/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 32w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/48x32/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 48w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/64x43/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 64w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/96x64/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 96w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/128x85/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 128w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/256x171/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 256w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/376x251/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 376w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/384x256/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 384w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/415x277/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 415w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/480x320/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 480w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/540x360/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 540w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/640x427/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 640w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/750x500/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 750w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/828x552/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 828w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/1080x720/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 1080w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/1200x800/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 1200w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/1440x960/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 1440w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/1920x1280/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 1920w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/2048x1365/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 2048w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/2400x1600/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg 2400w" src="https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/2400x1600/filters:focal(1004x1335:1005x1336):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9876511/postnetfinal.jpg"/></noscript></span></figure></div></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph my-12 font-fkroman text-17 leading-150 text-gray-13 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">Yesterday, FCC chairman Ajit Pai successfully led a vote to repeal the Open Internet Order, effectively killing net neutrality rules. The full order hasn’t been released, but advocacy groups are already preparing for the fight to defend a neutral internet once Title II is repealed. Passing net neutrality protections in 2015 was relatively straightforward, but getting those protections back requires going through every potential legal avenue. Meanwhile, ISPs will be testing their ability to control internet traffic — possibly in very blatant ways.</p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph my-12 font-fkroman text-17 leading-150 text-gray-13 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white"><strong>Lawsuits are coming</strong></p></div><span class="mb-8 font-polysans text-15 font-medium leading-150 tracking-1 text-gray-13 "><a class="inline-block shadow-underline-black hover:shadow-highlight-franklin" href="/2017/12/15/16780564/net-neutrality-is-dead-what-happens-next">Read Article &gt;</a></span></div></div></div></li><li role="article" class="mx-[-16px] mb-40 mt-[-40px] px-16 last:mb-0 md:mx-0 md:px-0" id="stream-entry-90bfd754-6cc9-42a4-bf50-07af2a774fae"><div class="border-solid border-blurple-df pt-40 sm:border-b-0 border-b"><div class="mb-40"><div><div class="mb-10 flex items-center"><div class="absolute left-[-2px] hidden h-6 w-12 border-y-2 border-white bg-[#DFCFFF] md:block"></div><div class="relative mr-8 block h-[36px] w-[36px] flex-none overflow-hidden rounded-full border border-solid border-gray-ef bg-[#DFCFFF]"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0"><img alt="Sarah Jeong" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" class="rounded-full" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover"/><noscript><img alt="Sarah Jeong" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover" class="rounded-full" sizes="36px" srcSet="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/LETYSgAohc7ojj-3MgQIWPk-bDI=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195220/jbareham_171019_2072_0099..0.jpg 16w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/LETYSgAohc7ojj-3MgQIWP