/div></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph my-12 font-fkroman text-17 leading-150 text-gray-13 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">The FCC is about to give massive internet service providers the power to divide the internet. It is at risk of becoming unrecognizable. A vital global utility that has been a boon to creative and economic freedom for people around the world may be turned into a twisted land of tolls and corporate control.</p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph my-12 font-fkroman text-17 leading-150 text-gray-13 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">The stakes are high. The internet now touches every town, every city, and every single one of us — whether we use it or not. Those who control the network control the future. </p></div><span class="mb-8 font-polysans text-15 font-medium leading-150 tracking-1 text-gray-13 "><a class="inline-block shadow-underline-black hover:shadow-highlight-franklin" href="/2017/12/11/16746230/net-neutrality-fcc-isp-congress-campaign-contribution">Read Article &gt;</a></span></div></div></div></li><li role="article" class="mx-[-16px] mb-40 mt-[-40px] px-16 last:mb-0 md:mx-0 md:px-0" id="stream-entry-cf502671-2b68-4ba5-87ca-460c8ff41ee9"><div class="border-solid border-blurple-df pt-40 sm:border-b-0 border-b"><div class="mb-40"><div><div class="mb-10 flex items-center"><div class="absolute left-[-2px] hidden h-6 w-12 border-y-2 border-white bg-[#DFCFFF] md:block"></div><div class="relative mr-8 block h-[36px] w-[36px] flex-none overflow-hidden rounded-full border border-solid border-gray-ef bg-[#DFCFFF]"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0"><img alt="" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" class="rounded-full" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover"/><noscript><img alt="" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover" class="rounded-full" sizes="36px" srcSet="/icons/default_headshot.png 16w, /icons/default_headshot.png 32w, /icons/default_headshot.png 48w, /icons/default_headshot.png 64w, /icons/default_headshot.png 96w, /icons/default_headshot.png 128w, /icons/default_headshot.png 256w, /icons/default_headshot.png 376w, /icons/default_headshot.png 384w, /icons/default_headshot.png 415w, /icons/default_headshot.png 480w, /icons/default_headshot.png 540w, /icons/default_headshot.png 640w, /icons/default_headshot.png 750w, /icons/default_headshot.png 828w, /icons/default_headshot.png 1080w, /icons/default_headshot.png 1200w, /icons/default_headshot.png 1440w, /icons/default_headshot.png 1920w, /icons/default_headshot.png 2048w, /icons/default_headshot.png 2400w" src="/icons/default_headshot.png"/></noscript></span></div><div class="font-polysans text-11 uppercase leading-130 tracking-12 text-blurple"><p class="mb-2 font-bold">Dec 8, 2017</p><p><span><a class="hover:shadow-underline-blurple" href="/authors/amelia-holowaty-krales">Amelia H. Krales</a></span><span><span> and </span><a class="hover:shadow-underline-blurple" href="/authors/michael-zelenko">Michael Zelenko</a></span></p></div></div><h2 class="mb-16 mt-12 font-polysans text-22 font-bold leading-100 tracking-1 text-gray-13 md:mb-14 md:text-24"><a class="hover:shadow-underline-black" href="/2017/12/8/16751244/net-neutrality-verizon-protests-photos-fight-for-the-future">Photos from inside the Protect Net Neutrality protests</a></h2><div class="w-full shrink-0 lg:basis-[600px]"><div class="md:pl-0"><figure class="duet--article--lede-image w-full"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:relative"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;padding-top:66.63636363636364%"></span><img alt="" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding="async" data-nimg="responsive" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover"/><noscript><img alt="" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-nimg="responsive" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover" sizes="(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 100px), (max-width: 1180px) 700px, 600px" srcSet="https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/16x11/filters:focal(1025x1329:1026x1330):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/9831581/akrales_171207_2184_0285.jpg 16w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2040x1360/32x21/filters:focal(1025x1329:102