99/Net_Neutrality_GIF_v04.gif 1200w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1800x1200/1440x960/filters:focal(914x1064:915x1065):no_upscale():format(webp)/cdn0.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/8602199/Net_Neutrality_GIF_v04.gif 1440w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1800x1200/1920x1280/filters:focal(914x1064:915x1065):no_upscale():format(webp)/cdn0.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/8602199/Net_Neutrality_GIF_v04.gif 1920w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1800x1200/2048x1365/filters:focal(914x1064:915x1065):no_upscale():format(webp)/cdn0.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/8602199/Net_Neutrality_GIF_v04.gif 2048w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1800x1200/2400x1600/filters:focal(914x1064:915x1065):no_upscale():format(webp)/cdn0.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/8602199/Net_Neutrality_GIF_v04.gif 2400w" src="https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1800x1200/2400x1600/filters:focal(914x1064:915x1065):no_upscale():format(webp)/cdn0.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/8602199/Net_Neutrality_GIF_v04.gif"/></noscript></span></figure></div></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph my-12 font-fkroman text-17 leading-150 text-gray-13 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">FCC chairman Ajit Pai is fond of saying that “the internet was not broken in 2015” when he argues for repeal of our nation’s net neutrality rules. This is particularly funny to me, because in 2014 I literally wrote an article called “<a href="/2014/2/25/5431382/the-internet-is-fucked">The internet is fucked</a>.”</p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph my-12 font-fkroman text-17 leading-150 text-gray-13 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">Why was it fucked? Because the free and open internet was in danger of becoming tightly controlled by giant telecom corporations that were already doing things like blocking apps and services from phones and excusing their own services from data caps. Because the lack of competition in the internet access market let these companies act like predatory monopolies. And because our government lacked the will or clarity to just say what everyone already knows: internet access is a utility.</p></div><span class="mb-8 font-polysans text-15 font-medium leading-150 tracking-1 text-gray-13 "><a class="inline-block shadow-underline-black hover:shadow-highlight-franklin" href="/2017/7/12/15715030/what-is-net-neutrality-fcc-ajit-pai-bill-rules-repealed">Read Article &gt;</a></span></div></div></div></li><li role="article" class="mx-[-16px] mb-40 mt-[-40px] px-16 last:mb-0 md:mx-0 md:px-0" id="stream-entry-737f126b-4794-4ef5-ba03-2dc5cba2560d"><div class="border-solid border-blurple-df pt-40 sm:border-b-0 border-b"><div class="mb-40"><div><div class="mb-10 flex items-center"><div class="absolute left-[-2px] hidden h-6 w-12 border-y-2 border-white bg-[#DFCFFF] md:block"></div><div class="relative mr-8 block h-[36px] w-[36px] flex-none overflow-hidden rounded-full border border-solid border-gray-ef bg-[#DFCFFF]"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0"><img alt="Jacob Kastrenakes" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" class="rounded-full" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-s