sset/file/13073627/462755476.0.1423675951.jpg 1920w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:5184x3456/2048x1365/filters:focal(2592x1728:2593x1729):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/13073627/462755476.0.1423675951.jpg 2048w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:5184x3456/2400x1600/filters:focal(2592x1728:2593x1729):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/13073627/462755476.0.1423675951.jpg 2400w" src="https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:5184x3456/2400x1600/filters:focal(2592x1728:2593x1729):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/13073627/462755476.0.1423675951.jpg"/></noscript></span><div class="duet--media--caption pt-6 font-polysans-mono text-12 font-light leading-130 tracking-1"> <cite class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup inline not-italic text-gray-63 dark:text-gray-bd [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-gray-63 [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-gray-bd dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-gray [&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray-63 dark:[&amp;&gt;a]:text-gray-bd dark:[&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray">Mark Wilson/Getty Images</cite></div></figure></div></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph my-12 font-fkroman text-17 leading-150 text-gray-13 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">The FCC has a problem. It wants to keep the internet equal and open — as it largely has been — but doing that requires making <em>rules</em>. And every time the FCC makes rules, it pisses someone off: Comcast, Verizon, the entire cable industry. Throw their names in a hat, pick one out, and you&#39;ve got a party that&#39;s ready for court. That&#39;s how the commission&#39;s last set of net neutrality rules were killed, and that&#39;s what it has to look forward to dealing with again in the very near future.</p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph my-12 font-fkroman text-17 leading-150 text-gray-13 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">That&#39;s because the FCC is back with <a href="http://www.theverge.com/2015/2/4/7977569/its-official-the-fcc-will-seek-to-reclassify-the-internet-as-a-utility">a whole new set of rules</a>. Rules that the general public loves but that the cable and wireless industries absolutely hate: it wants to reclassify internet service as a Title II &quot;telecommunications service&quot; — rather than a Title I &quot;information service,&quot; as the internet was declared back in 2002 — and thus make it subject to very strong regulations that can protect net neutrality.</p></div><span class="mb-8 font-polysans text-15 font-medium leading-150 tracking-1 text-gray-13 "><a class="inline-block shadow-underline-black hover:shadow-highlight-franklin" href="/2015/2/11/8019261/fcc-net-neutrality-title-ii-possible-trial-comcast-verizon">Read Article &gt;</a></span></div></div></div></li><li role="article" class="mx-[-16px] mb-40 mt-[-40px] px-16 last:mb-0 md:mx-0 md:px-0" id="stream-entry-279db0ed-b01e-4226-be40-61ecadc3bf4e"><div class="border-solid border-blurple-df pt-40 sm:border-b-0 border-b"><div class="mb-40"><div><div class="mb-10 flex items-center"><div class="absolute left-[-2px] hidden h-6 w-12 border-y-2 border-white bg-[#DFCFFF] md:block"></div><div class="relative mr-8 block h-[36px] w-[36px] flex-none overflow-hidden rounded-full border border-solid border-gray-ef bg-[#DFCFFF]"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0"><img alt="Adi Robertson" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" class="rounded-full" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover"/><noscript><img alt="Adi Robertson" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover" class="rounded-full" sizes="36px" srcSet="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/v33tpzondm_MBRbLGGZ8SIoPDeY=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195784/ADI_ROBERTSON.0.jpg 16w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/v33tpzondm_MBRbLGGZ8SIoPDeY=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195784/ADI_ROBERTSON.0.jpg 32w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/v33tpzondm_MBRbLGGZ8SIoPDeY=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195784/ADI_ROBERTSON.0.jpg 48w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/v33tpzondm_MBRbLGGZ8SIoPDeY=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195784/ADI_ROBERTSON.0.jpg 64w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/v33tpzondm_MBRbLGGZ8SIoPDeY=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195784/ADI_ROBERTSON.0.jpg 96w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/v33tpzondm_MBRbLGGZ8SIoPDeY=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195784/ADI_ROBERTSON.0.jpg 128w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/v33tpzondm_MBRbLGGZ8SIoPDeY=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195784/ADI_ROBERTSON.0.jpg 256w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/v33tpzondm_MBRbLGGZ8SIoPDeY=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/195784/ADI_ROBERTSON.0.jpg 376w, https://cdn.vox-